          "vnum": 325,
          "name": "Royal Smithery",
          "description": "The hot fires in the forges along the walls of the room lick at the stifling air. Shadows twist and dance across the stone walls. Large, heavy anvils sit near each iron oven, awaiting white hot steel. The mithril-melting heat is something a master metalsmith adjusts to throughout the course of his apprenticeship, but for you, a common adventurer, it is nearly unbearable. Tools are arranged neatly throughout the large room, though their sheer number makes them appear haphazardly strewn about.",
